examples.en: He made no reply, but simply scowled.
Mum scowled at him and refused to say anything.
The girl scowled at me, then stuck out her tongue.
He scowled down at the misbehaving child.
The teacher scowled at the children, making them afraid of him.
Mallard scowled at him. He had never learned to receive compliment or expressions of gratitude gracefully.
Patrick scowled, but did as he was told.
